The Sheriff of the Court attaches property at the Emfuleni Local Municipality as part of a 635-million Eskom debt. EMFULENI - Eskom is taking strong measures against government entities to recover debt. The power utility has promised to recover billions of rands owed in unpaid bills. READ: Emfuleni mayor admits to wasteful expenditure On Tuesday, a court order was enforced and property attached at the Emfuleni municipality head offices for non-payment. The municipality located in Gauteng owes R635-million to the power utility.